BHP Billiton Ltd.



 OVERVIEW



Date Founded


2001




Headquarters


Bhp Billiton Centre, 180 Lonsdale Street, Melbourne, Victoria (vic) 3000




Type of Company



                                                                    Public
                                                            




Employees (Worldwide)


65.3K




Industries


Non-Energy Mining & Minerals

Oil & Gas




Company Description


BHP Billiton Ltd. engages in the exploration, development, production and processing of iron ore, metallurgical coal, copper and uranium. It operates through the following segments: Petroleum and Potash, Copper, Iron Ore, and Coal. The Petroleum and Potash segment explores, develops and produces oil and gas; plus the pre-development of Potash. The Copper segment mines copper, silver, lead, zinc, molybdenum, uranium and gold. The Iron Ore segment mines iron ore. The Coal segment mines metallurgical coal and thermal coal. The company was founded on June 29, 2001 and it is headquartered in Melbourne, Australia.




Website


http://www.bhp.com/






